com.ibm.team.process.common.advice
Interface IReportInfo

All Superinterfaces:
org.eclipse.core.runtime.IAdaptable
All Known Subinterfaces:
IAdvisorInfo
public interface IReportInfo
extends org.eclipse.core.runtime.IAdaptable

A report info reports information for an operation, operation advisor, or operation participant. The information reported has an associated severity.

Factory methods to create report infos are available on IParticipantInfoCollector. Implementors of IOperationParticipant are passed such a collector when they are run.

Clients may not implement this interface.

Since:
0.6

getSeverity

int getSeverity()
Returns the severity of this info. The severity values are as follows:
  • IProcessReport.OK - this info reports success
  • IProcessReport.WARNING - this info reports a problem which is not serious
  • IProcessReport.ERROR - this info reports a serious problem

Returns:
the severity of this info

setSeverity

void setSeverity(int severity)
Sets the severity of this info.

Rather than setting an info's severity directly, IOperationParticipant and IOperationAdvisor implementors should should use the available factory methods on the collectors which they are passed. The collectors set an appropriate severity.

This method may only be called by an operation participant or advisor, and only before the info has been added to a collector. If this method is called after the info has been added to a collector, there is no guarantee that the containing report's severity will be updated.

The given value must be one of the value defined on IReportInfo.getSeverity().

Parameters:
severity - the severity to set

setData

void setData(java.lang.String data)
Sets the data field of this info. Clients can use this field to store an arbitrary string which will be preserved if this info is passed over the wire.

This field is typically used for carrying structured information in an info (for example, XML).

This support is experimental and is likely to be broken.

Parameters:
data - the string data

getProblemObject

java.lang.Object getProblemObject()
Returns the advisor-specific object associated with this problem or null if none is available. This data will not be preserved over the wire.

This support is experimental and is likely to be broken.

Returns:
the advisor-specific data associated with this problem

setProblemObject

void setProblemObject(java.lang.Object object)
Sets the object field of this problem. Clients can use this field to store an arbitrary object which is associated with infos they create. This data will not be preserved over the wire.

This field is typically used by client-side operation advisors to hold onto data which can be useful to a UI presentation or to a problem resolution.

This support is experimental and is likely to be broken.
